# ==========================================
# 1. Node.js / React (Frontend)
# ==========================================
**/node_modules/
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/.pnpm-debug.log*

# Vite / Build outputs
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.local

# Development environment variables
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local
**/.env.development
**/.env.production

# ==========================================
# 2. .NET / ASP.NET Core (Backend)
# ==========================================
# Build & publish outputs
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/publish/
**/out/

# Visual Studio / VS Code
**/.vs/
**/.vscode/
*.[Dd]erived
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# Rider / JetBrains
**/.idea/

# Test results
**/TestResults/
**/*.trx
**/*.coverage
**/*.coveragexml

# ==========================================
# 3. Configuration & Secrets
# ==========================================
# Never commit secrets or environment-specific config
**/appsettings.Development.json
**/appsettings.local.json
**/appsettings.Production.json
**/secrets.json
# Keep appsettings.json only if it contains no secrets.
# Uncomment the next line to also exclude the base config:
# **/appsettings.json

# User secrets (dotnet user-secrets)
**/secrets/

# ==========================================
# 4. Uploaded User Files (wwwroot/uploads)
# ==========================================
# Files uploaded by users at runtime are NOT source code.
# They are large binary blobs (images, PDFs, DOCX, etc.)
# that would bloat the repository history.
**/wwwroot/uploads/*

# Keep the uploads directory itself so the app has the folder
# on a fresh clone (static file middleware needs it to exist).
!**/wwwroot/uploads/.gitkeep

# ==========================================
# 5. EF Core Migrations
# ==========================================
# Migrations are auto-generated by "dotnet ef migrations add".
# Committing them causes merge conflicts and schema drift.
# Each developer/environment should run "dotnet ef database update" locally.
**/Migrations/

# ==========================================
# 6. Database / SQL Server Local Artifacts
# ==========================================
*.mdf
*.ldf
*.sdf
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# ==========================================
# 7. Logs & Temporary Files
# ==========================================
*.log
**/logs/
**/tmp/
**/temp/
*.tmp
*.bak
*.swp
*.orig

# OS generated files
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Icon?
Desktop.ini